commit.message:
Documentation improvements

As suggested by G.W. Haywood.

Perl 5.26 no longer has "." in @INC by default.

Hence, we need to stuff it ourselves.
Added a pattern for postal codes of Luxembourg

Ignore csv files.

Since we have postal code data from Luxembourg in CSV format.

Extract postal codes from Luxembourg.

The Luxembourg Post distributes a CSV file with all postal codes.
Improved pattern for German postal codes.
Improve pattern for Italian postal codes.

Improve formatting of patterns:

  - Make formatting work indenpendent on how many digits are matched.
  - Deal with long lines which may need to be broken more than once.
Format ranges depending on the width of the postal code.
Mention another source of postal code data

Add postal code 9489 to Liechtenstein.

The data source used to extract the postal code data has, for
Switzerland/Liechtenstein, the postal code 9489 filed under Switzerland.
However, this postal code belongs to Schaan Log, which is located in
Liechtenstein (all postal codes 948x and 949x are for Liechtenstein).
Add BUILD_REQUIRES, CONFIGURE_REQUIRES and TEST_REQUIRES arguments.

Get prereqs in META_MERGE to actually merge.

The trick is to add C<< "meta-spec" => {version => 2} >> in META_MERGE.
